caption.text:
(night thought)
how many times do you see your reflection in a mirror and not liking what you see?
for me, it was so often.
i was so insecure back then, i rarely took picture of myself.
there was always something to be insecure about; acne, thigh gap, under eye circle, etc.

until i finally realized that it wasn't right.
it wasn't right to not accepting my flaws, it wasn't right to hide away.
i decided to love myself.
it was not easy, but the journey of loving myself feels.... deliberating. 
i feel free.

caption.text:
airing my heart out

the truth is i'm anxious, thrilled, excited, scared, grateful, sad, and so many more emotions mixed in one. it's overwhelming. excited for whatever comes in life, but scared of the result. sad because of disappointment, but grateful for everything life has offered.

there are so many uncertainty in life, sometimes i can't keep up. one day i got everything under control, the next day i don't. it's confusing and that's okay. it's okay to be sad, to have feelings, to be vulnerable, and to not have your shit together at all times.
it's okay to make mistake, as you'll learn your lesson and improve
it's okay to be broken, as you'll pick up the pieces and rise again
and lastly, it's okay to love, as you'll learn to forgive and heal.
